  "body": "1. Users should be able to choose a fleet, ie `eth.prod`, `eth.test`, `eth.staging`. Nodes to be selected should come from https://fleets.status.im\r\n2. Download the json at https://fleets.status.im and use it to update bootnodes, rendezvous nodes, mailservers, and whisper servers in the node config (update the values in `constants.NODE_CONFIG`, then `saveSetting(Setting.NodeConfig, updatedConfig)`. To obtain feature parity with mobile, this should be done for the following events:\r\n   a. On fleet change (#1 above)\r\n   b. On network change\r\n  However, maybe we could/should also do this on login so that we have the most up-to-date nodes. The reason on login and not app start is because the existing node config must be merged with the fleet data and then saved in a setting `node-config`, and the `get` and `set` of settings requires a running status-go node.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n1. The crux of updating the node config in status-react can be found here: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/920bc7d93ec2ea096321379c51cfe8b104a50704/src/status_im/node/core.cljs#L87-L147. Note that not ALL boot/rendezvous/mailserver/whisper nodes are merged with the node config.\r\n2. `fleets.json` download in `status-react` is handled through a `make update-fleets` target: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/920bc7d93ec2ea096321379c51cfe8b104a50704/Makefile#L142-L145",
